verbose_text: There was a significant, but transient, increase in the levels of miR-124 in the heart at 2 h post delivery (~ 40- to 170-fold for 1 nmol and 10 nmol doses, both p < 0.0001 vs. veh ctrl), which subsequently disappeared at the later 24 h and 48 h endpoints for both the 1 and 10 nmol / rat doses.
